            . I am servant to James Greig; he is a <rs id="t18300415-318-viclabel1740" type="occupation">baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-318-victim2667 t18300415-318-viclabel1740"></join>. I was sitting in the parlour behind the shop, at half-past seven o'clock in the evening, and heard money chinking - I got up, and saw a <rs id="t18300415-318-deflabel1741" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-318-defend2665 t18300415-318-deflabel1741"></join> run out with the till in his hand; I ran to the door, and called Stop thief! he set the till down four or five doors off, and ran away - the next witness brought him back; I had not seen his face -I saw no other boy; I saw him when the witness pursued him; the till was taken up, and brought to me - we could not tell whether any thing was missing from it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-318-person2669">
